// =============================================================================
// core/database/sqlite/native/backup/mod.vr
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 7 (consumer-facing — `Database.backup_to(target)`)
// Spec: sqlite-native.md §22 — operational tooling; §6 — file format
//
// Online backup, the loom analogue of `sqlite3_online_backup`.
//
// The protocol is page-by-page: a `BackupEngineHandle` is initialised
// against a (source, target) connection pair, then stepped one or
// more pages at a time. While stepping, the source connection
// continues to take writes; pages already copied that get dirtied
// are simply re-read from the source on the next step.
//
// Submodules:
//   * `state`   — BackupEngineHandle state machine + step result
//   * `policy`  — throttle policy (pages-per-step, sleep-between)
//   * `progress` — observable counters
// =============================================================================

module core.database.sqlite.native.backup;

public module state;
public module policy;
public module progress;
